    },
    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The sparse texture to update.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "texture"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A mode that indicates whether the method allocates or frees a memory tile in the texture.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "mode"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A region, in tile coordinates, that describes the part of the mipmap to update.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "region"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The mipmap to update.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "mipLevel"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The slice in the texture to update.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "slice"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When the GPU executes the command that updates the texture’s memory mapping, the GPU gets details about the region from the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "region",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To allocate tiles from the heap, pass ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLSparseTextureMappingMode/map",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " as the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "mode",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter, and to free files back to the heap, pass ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLSparseTextureMappingMode/unmap",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you encode other commands that use the texture’s contents, such as rendering to the texture or sampling from a texture, synchronize the texture’s mapping updates with those commands to avoid race conditions. See ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/resource-synchronization",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you encode commands with multiple resource state passes, synchronize the resources to run the commands in the passes sequentially. See the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLResourceStateCommandEncoder",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
